{"title_page": "2006 Taipei International Invitational Futsal Tournament", "text_new": "[[File:Taipei Gymnasium 20130403.jpg|thumb|[[Taipei Gymnasium]]]]\n\nThe '''Taipei International Invitational Futsal Tournament''' ({{zh|t=\u53f0\u5317\u570b\u969b\u4e94\u4eba\u5236\u8db3\u7403\u9080\u8acb\u8cfd}}) was held from October 27 to October 29, 2006 at [[Taipei Gymnasium]] in [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]]. It was the first international [[futsal]] event in Taipei after holding the [[FIFA Futsal World Cup 2004|2004 FIFA Futsal World Championship]].<ref name=\"futsalplanet\">{{cite news\n |title = Taipei International Invitational Futsal Tournament\n |url = http://www.futsalplanet.com/news/news-01.asp?id=6606\n |publisher = [[Futsal Planet]]\n |date = 2006-10-23\n |access-date = 2006-10-30\n |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070927194901/http://www.futsalplanet.com/news/news-01.asp?id=6606\n |archive-date = 2007-09-27\n |url-status = dead\n }}</ref> Finally, Japanese [[D.C Asahikawa Futsal Club]] beat [[Macau Football Association|Macau]], [[Chinese Taipei Football Association|Chinese Taipei]], and [[Taipei Futsal Association|Taipei Select team]] and won the first place. \n\nBefore the tournament was held, the organizers originally wanted to invite [[Korea Football Association|Korea national team]] as well as Macau national team and D.C Asahikawa. However, the Korea team declined the invitation, and thus [[Taipei Futsal Association]]'s select team was included as the replacement.<ref name=\"futsalplanet\"/>\n\nIn December, [[Chinese Taipei Football Association]] was fined US$ 10,000 by [[Asian Football Confederation|AFC]] Disciplinary Committee for failing to seek the AFC\u2019s approval for the tournament which violates Article 11-V (Tournaments) of the Regulations governing the application of AFC Statutes \u2018All tournaments involving more than two local or national teams (clubs or representative teams) which belong to difference member associations must be approved by the Confederation.'<ref>{{cite news\n|title=AFC Disciplinary Committee fines Bahrain, Pakistan and Chinese Taipei FAs\n|url=http://www.the-afc.com/english/media/default.asp?mnsection=media&section=newsDetails&newsID=7596\n|publisher=[[Asian Football Confederation]]\n|date=2006-12-07\n}}</ref>\n\n==Tournament table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|ptsfirst=y\n\n|team1=ASA|name_ASA=[[D.C Asahikawa Futsal Club|D.C Asahikawa]] ([[Japan]])\n|team2=TPE|name_TPE=[[Taipei Futsal Association|Taipei Select]]\n|team3=CTP|name_CTP=[[Chinese Taipei Football Association|Chinese Taipei]]\n|team4=MAC|name_MAC=[[Macau Football Association|Macau]]\n|win_ASA=3|draw_ASA=0|loss_ASA=0|gf_ASA=26|ga_ASA=4\n|win_TPE=2|draw_TPE=0|loss_TPE=1|gf_TPE=8|ga_TPE=8\n|win_CTP=1|draw_CTP=0|loss_CTP=2|gf_CTP=5|ga_CTP=9\n|win_MAC=0|draw_MAC=0|loss_MAC=3|gf_MAC=0|ga_MAC=18\n\n|col_C=green1|text_C=\n|result1=C\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Results==\n{{footballbox \n| date = October 27, 2006<br/>18:00 \n| team1 = [[Taipei Futsal Association|Taipei Select]]\n| score = 2 - 8\n| report = [http://www.ltsports.com.tw/newweb/news.asp?no=49884&N_Class=4 (Results)]\n| team2 = [[D.C Asahikawa Futsal Club|D.C Asahikawa]]\n| goals1 = [[Wang Chi-cheng]] (\u738b\u5409\u6210) {{goal|15}}<br/>[[Ho Kuo-chen]] (\u4f55\u570b\u798e) {{goal|?}}\n| goals2 = [[Yuta Saga|Y. Saga]] (\u5d6f\u5ce8\u7950\u592a) {{goal|16}}<br/>[[Takahiro Takayama|T. Takayama]] (\u9ad8\u5c71\u525b\u5bec) {{goal|19}}<br/>[[Yukihiro Sakashi|Y. Sakashi]] (\u9152\u5e2b\u5e78\u88d5) {{goal|19}}<br/>[[Hirofumi Sasaki|H. Sasaki]] (\u4f50\u4f50\u6728\u6d0b\u6587) {{goal|22}}<br/>[[Yuta Saga|Y. Saga]] (\u5d6f\u5ce8\u7950\u592a) {{goal|29}}<br/>[[Norihiro Arai|N. Arai]] (\u8352\u4e95\u7d00\u5f18) {{goal|?}}<br/>? {{goal|?}}<br/>? {{goal|?}}\n| stadium = [[Taipei Gymnasium]], [[Taipei]]\n}}\n----\n{{footballbox \n| date = October 27, 2006<br/>20:00 \n| team1 = [[Chinese Taipei Football Association|Chinese Taipei]]\n| sco