/2006_Taipei_International_Invitational_Futsal_Tournament"}
{"title_page": "Rose Kabagyenyi", "text_new": "{{short description|Ugandan politician}}\n'''Rose Kabagyenyi'''  (born 4 August 1974) is a [[Uganda|Ugandan]] [[politician]] and woman [[Member of Parliament]]. In 2011, she was elected as a woman representative in [[Parliament of Uganda|Parliament]] for the [[Kisoro District]].\n\nShe is a member of the ruling [[National Resistance Movement]] [[political party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observer.ug/news/headlines/56437-age-limit-how-your-mp-voted|title=Age limit: How your MP voted|last=Observer|first=The|website=The Observer - Uganda|accessdate=2020-03-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrm.ug/organ/nrm-parliamentary-caucus|title=NRM PARLIAMENTAL CAUCUS|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nShe completed her [[Primary school|primary level]] education from Gikoro primary school in 1987. In 1990, she completed her [[Uganda Certificate of Education]] (UCE) for lower [[secondary education]] at the [https://www.paceproject.net/pace-news/seseme-girls-secondary-school-in-kisoro-uganda/ Seseme Girls secondary school] in [[Kisoro District|Kisoro]]. \n\nShe attained her first certificate in [[Agriculture]] in 1995 and a [[diploma]] in agriculture from the [https://www.studenthub.ug/institutions/89/bukalasa-agricultural-college Bukalasa Agricultural college] in 2000. \n\nIn 2004, Kabagyenyi achieved a [[Bachelor of Engineering|bachelor's]] degree in [[Agriculture]] from the [[Makerere University]] in [[Kampala]]. She went further with her studies and obtained her second diploma in 2011 and a second certificate in Monitoring and Evaluation in 2013 from [[Uganda Management Institute]].\n\nIn 2014, Kabagyenyi earned herself a [[Master's degree]] in [[Agriculture]] from [[Makerere University]].\n<br />\n\n== Work experience and other responsibilities ==\nFrom 1997 to 2000, Kabagyenyi worked as the Agricultural officer for the Kisoro local government and as a district agricultural officer for the Kisoro District from 2007 to 2010.\n\nRose served as a consultant for National Agricultural Advisory Services (NAADS).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201006160047.html|title=Irish Potato Prices Shoot Up|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naads.or.ug/|title=National Agricultural Advisory Services \u2013 Promoting Profitable Agricultural Production|last=ea_admin|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n\n[[Category:Ugandan women in politics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Uganda]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Makerere University alumni]]\n[[Category:National Resistance Movement politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century women politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Under review|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|Ugandan politician}}\n'''Rose Kabagyenyi'''  (born 4 August 1974) is a [[Uganda|Ugandan]] [[politician]] and woman [[Member of Parliament]]. In 2011, she was elected as a woman representative in [[Parliament of Uganda|Parliament]] for the [[Kisoro District]].\n\nShe is a member of the ruling [[National Resistance Movement]] [[political party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observer.ug/news/headlines/56437-age-limit-how-your-mp-voted|title=Age limit: How your MP voted|last=Observer|first=The|website=The Observer - Uganda|accessdate=2020-03-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrm.ug/organ/nrm-parliamentary-caucus|title=NRM PARLIAMENTAL CAUCUS|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nShe completed her [[Primary school|primary level]] education from Gikoro primary school in 1987. In 1990, she completed her [[Uganda Certificate of Education]] (UCE) for lower [[secondary education]] at the [https://www.paceproject.net/pace-news/seseme-girls-secondary-school-in-kisoro-uganda/ Seseme Girls secondary school] in [[Kisoro District|Kisoro]]. \n\nShe attained her first certificate in [[Agriculture]] in 1995 and a [[diploma]] in agriculture from the [https://www.studenthub.ug/institutions/89/bukalasa-agricultural-college Bukalasa Agricultural college] in 2000. \n\nIn 2004, Kabagyenyi achieved a [[Bachelor of Engineering|bachelor's]] degree in [[Agriculture]] from the [[Makerere University]] in [[Kampala]]. She went further with her studies and obtained her second diploma in 2011 and a second certificate in Monitoring and Evaluation in 2013 from [[Uganda Management Institute]].\n\nIn 2014, Kabagyenyi earned herself a [[Master's degree]] in [[Agriculture]] from [[Makerere University]].\n<br />\n\n== Work experience and other responsibilities ==\nFrom 1997 to 2000, Kabagyenyi worked as the Agricultural officer for the Kisoro local government and as a district agricultural officer for the Kisoro District from 2007 to 2010.\n\nRose served as a consultant for National Agricultural Advisory Services (NAADS).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201006160047.html|title=Irish Potato Prices Shoot Up|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naads.or.ug/|title=National Agricultural Advisory Services \u2013 Promoting Profitable Agricultural Production|last=ea_admin|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n\n[[Category:Ugandan women in politics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Uganda]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Makerere University alumni]]\n[[Category:National Resistance Movement politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century women politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Lefcentreright", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_Kabagyenyi"}
{"title_page": "Dota Underlords", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title     = Dota Underlords\n| image     = Dota Underlords steam.jpg\n| developer = [[Valve Corporation|Valve]]\n| publisher = Valve\n| designer  =\n| writer    =\n| composer  =\n| engine    = [[Source 2]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Android (operating system)|Android]]|[[iOS]]|[[macOS]]|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[Linux]]}}\n| released  = February 25, 2020\n| genre     = [[Auto battler]]\n| modes     = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n| series    = ''[[Dota]]''\n}}\n'''''Dota Underlords''''' is an [[auto battler]] game developed and published by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[macOS]], [[Microsoft Windows]], and [[Linux]]. The game is based on a popular ''[[Dota 2]]'' community created game mode called ''[[Dota Auto Chess]]'', which was released in January 2019. ''Dota Underlords'' was first released [[free-to-play]] in [[early access]] in June 2019 before officially releasing on February 25, 2020.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Dota Underlords'' is an [[auto battler]], a [[chess]]-inspired competitive [[strategy video game|strategy game]], where players place characters, known as heroes, on an 8x8 grid-shaped battlefield. After a preparation phase, a team's heroes then automatically fight the opposing team without any further direct input from the player.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\">{{cite web |last1=Gilroy |first1=Joab |title=An Introduction to Auto Chess, Teamfight Tactics and Dota Underlords |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/07/04/a-guide-to-auto-chess-tft-league-of-legends-teamfight-tactics-dota-underlords |website=IGN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704045655/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/07/04/a-guide-to-auto-chess-tft-league-of-legends-teamfight-tactics-dota-underlords |archive-date=July 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A match features up to eight players online who take turns playing against each other in a one-on-one format, with the winner being the final player standing after eliminating all of the opposing heroes.<ref name=\"EGrules\">{{cite web |last1=Makar |first1=Connor |title=Dota Underlords guide: Strategies for how to play Dota Underlords, from getting gold to when to buy XP and unit upgrades |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-07-08-dota-underlords-guide-how-to-play-strategies-6037 |website=Eurogamer |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709212250/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-07-08-dota-underlords-guide-how-to-play-strategies-6037 |archive-date=July 9, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to the online [[matchmaking]], single-player matches against [[Video game bot|bots]] is also featured, as well as a \"freestyle\" practice mode that puts no limits on hero combinations.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/><ref name=\"Duos\">{{cite web |last1=Tan Guan Hao |first1=Dexter |title=Dota Underlords gets 2 new game modes for The Big Update |url=https://dotesports.com/dota-2/news/dota-underlords-gets-two-new-game-modes-for-the-big-update |website=Dot Esports |accessdate=October 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022173448/https://dotesports.com/dota-2/news/dota-underlords-gets-two-new-game-modes-for-the-big-update |archive-date=October 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Over the course of a match, players earn gold and [[experience points]], which are used to upgrade heroes and other playable units to make them stronger.<ref name=\"EGrules\"/> Players also make use of [[Item (gaming)|items]], which give stat bonuses to units.<ref name=\"EGrules\"/> The game also features a \"duos\" mode, allowing two players on separate boards, but sharing health and levels, to perform as a team, with the winning duo having the best combined damage totals by the end.<ref name=\"Duos\"/>\n\n==Development and release==\n''Dota Underlords'' was developed and published by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[macOS]], [[Microsoft Windows]], and [[Linux]]. It is based on ''[[Dota Auto Chess]]'', a popular community created game mode within ''[[Dota 2]]'', a game they also developed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bolding |first1=Jonathan |title=A Dota 2 custom mode may be 2019's most popular new game |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/a-dota-2-custom-mode-may-be-2019s-most-popular-new-game/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190122195616/https://www.pcgamer.com/a-dota-2-custom-mode-may-be-2019s-most-popular-new-game/ |archive-date=January 22, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Warr |first1=Philippa |title=Dota Auto Chess: The joyful deck-based Dota 2 game that Artifact isn't |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-auto-chess-the-joyful-deck-based-dota-2-game-that-artifact-isnt/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=February 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190208131821/https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-auto-chess-the-joyful-deck-based-dota-2-game-that-artifact-isnt/ |archive-date=February 8, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Sullivan |first1=Lucas |title=The skyrocketing rise of Auto Chess, a Dota 2 custom map that became one of the year's biggest games |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/dota-auto-chess/ |website=GamesRadar+ |accessdate=April 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412164930/https://www.gamesradar.com/dota-auto-chess/ |archive-date=April 12, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Following ''Dota Auto Chess''{{'s}} release in January 2019, it quickly become a phenomenon, having over seven million players by April 2019, Valve had met with the mod's developers, the Chinese-based Drodo Studio, to discuss directly collaborating on a standalone version. However, the two companies were unable to come to an agreement, with them both stating that it was in their best interest to develop their own separate games, with ''Dota Underlords'' being Valve's project.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gilliam |first1=Ryan |title=Auto Chess creators bringing stand-alone game to PC later this year |url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/10/18660080/auto-chess-pc-epic-game-store-pc-gaming-show-e3-2019 |website=Polygon |accessdate=June 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611121202/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/10/18660080/auto-chess-pc-epic-game-store-pc-gaming-show-e3-2019 |archive-date=June 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The game was built using Valve's [[Source 2]] game engine, making it the first game using that engine to be released on mobile platforms.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bailey |first1=Dustin |title=The Dota Underlords open beta is now live |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/open-beta |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710192913/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/open-beta |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nValve announced ''Dota Underlords'' in May 2019, with it releasing in [[early access]] as a [[free-to-play]] game on June 20, 2019.<ref>{{cite web | last = Grayson | first = Nathan | title = Valve Is Making Its Own Version Of Dota Auto Chess | date = May 20, 2019 | url = https://kotaku.com/valve-is-making-its-own-version-of-dota-auto-chess-1834934135 | website = Kotaku | accessdate = May 21, 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190522173226/https://kotaku.com/valve-is-making-its-own-version-of-dota-auto-chess-1834934135 | archive-date = May 22, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Valve's Auto Chess competitor is Dota Underlords |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/13/18678182/dota-underlords-valve-auto-chess-open-beta-platforms |website=Polygon |accessdate=June 13, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190613222336/https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/13/18678182/dota-underlords-valve-auto-chess-open-beta-platforms |archive-date=June 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> where it saw over 1.5 million downloads and held a [[concurrent player count]] on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] of over 200,000 within a few days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Minotti |first1=Mike |title=Sensor Tower: Dota Underlords sees 1.5 million downloads in first week |url=https://venturebeat.com/2019/06/28/sensor-tower-dota-underlords-sees-1-5-million-downloads-in-first-week/ |website=VentureBeat |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630223055/https://venturebeat.com/2019/06/28/sensor-tower-dota-underlords-sees-1-5-million-downloads-in-first-week/ |archive-date=June 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Ali |title=Dota Underlords' player count tops 200,000 in its opening weekend |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/player-count-update |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710184350/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/player-count-update |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Features such as a replay system, ranked [[matchmaking]], daily challenges and rewards, and a [[battle pass]] were added over time during its early access phase before it officially released on February 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dota Underlords update: what features are coming to Underlords soon? |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/update |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710184355/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/update |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Connor |first1=Alice |title=Dota Underlords rises out of early access today |url=https://venturebeat.com/2020/02/25/dota-underlords-season-one-kicks-off-with-battle-pass-and-more/ |website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref> It features full [[cross-platform play]] between its PC and mobile versions, with players able to freely start games on one and finish it on another.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lawler |first1=Richard |title=Valve's 'Dota Underlords' open beta launches on Android, iOS and PC |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/20/dota-underlords-beta/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624140452/https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/20/dota-underlords-beta/ |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]'' called it a clone of ''Dota Auto Chess'', stating that while they thought ''Underlords'' was more appealing to new players, the many similarities to the original mod could make it hard for veterans of the genre to see a reason to play ''Underlords'' over it, adding that games need to be more \"unique in order to survive\" in a niche genre.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gillia |first1=Ryan |title=Dota Underlords feels like a clone of Auto Chess |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/21/18683816/dota-underlords-auto-chess-clone |website=Polygon |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630042648/https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/21/18683816/dota-underlords-auto-chess-clone |archive-date=June 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Critics also compared and contrasted it with ''[[Artifact (video game)|Artifact]]'', another Valve-developed ''Dota'' spinoff game released around the same time that was seen as unsuccessful,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Fraser |title=Dota Underlords has more than double Artifact's peak player count |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-underlords-has-more-than-double-artifacts-peak-player-count/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623155728/https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-underlords-has-more-than-double-artifacts-peak-player-count/ |archive-date=June 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lawler |first1=Richard |title='Dota Underlords' has more people playing now than 'Artifact' ever did |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/21/dota-underlords/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624145532/http://www.engadget.com/2019/06/21/dota-underlords/ |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Grayson |first1=Nathan |title=Valve's New Auto Chess Game Is Already Way More Popular Than Artifact Ever Was |url=https://kotaku.com/valves-new-auto-chess-game-is-already-way-more-popular-1835739847 |website=Kotaku |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624125634/https://kotaku.com/valves-new-auto-chess-game-is-already-way-more-popular-1835739847 |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> as well as ''[[Teamfight Tactics]]'', the ''[[League of Legends]]'' take on the genre.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ye |first1=Josh |title=Auto battlers started with Dota Auto Chess and now Valve and Riot Games are joining in |url=https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/auto-battlers-started-dota-auto-chess-and-now-valve-and-riot-games-are-joining/article/3017888 |website=Abacus |accessdate=July 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717000924/https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/auto-battlers-started-dota-auto-chess-and-now-valve-and-riot-games-are-joining/article/3017888 |archive-date=July 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[IGN]]'' considered ''Underlords'' to be the easiest auto battler to get into as a novice due in part to its [[user interface]].<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.underlords.com/}}\n\n{{Dota}}\n{{Valve}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games}}\n\n[[Category:2020 video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Auto battler video games]]\n[[Category:Dota]]\n[[Category:Esports games]]\n[[Category:Fantasy video games]]\n[[Category:Free online games]]\n[[Category:Free-to-play video games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Linux games]]\n[[Category:Lua-scripted video games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Strategy video games]]\n[[Category:Source 2 games]]\n[[Category:Valve Corporation games]]\n[[Category:Video games containing battle passes]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games with cross-platform play]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Video games that support Vulkan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title     = Dota Underlords\n| image     = Dota Underlords steam.jpg\n| developer = [[Valve Corporation|Valve]]\n| publisher = Valve\n| designer  =\n| writer    =\n| composer  =\n| engine    = [[Source 2]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Android (operating system)|Android]]|[[iOS]]|[[macOS]]|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[Linux]]}}\n| released  = February 25, 2020\n| genre     = [[Auto battler]]\n| modes     = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n| series    = ''[[Dota]]''\n}}\n'''''Dota Underlords''''' is an [[auto battler]] game developed and published by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[macOS]], [[Microsoft Windows]], and [[Linux]]. The game is based on a popular ''[[Dota 2]]'' community created game mode called ''[[Dota Auto Chess]]'', which was released in January 2019. ''Dota Underlords'' was first released [[free-to-play]] in [[early access]] in June 2019 before officially releasing on February 25, 2020.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Dota Underlords'' is an [[auto battler]], a [[chess]]-inspired competitive [[strategy video game|strategy game]], where players place characters known as \"heroes\" on an 8x8 grid-shaped battlefield. After a preparation phase, a team's heroes then automatically fight the opposing team without any further direct input from the player.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\">{{cite web |last1=Gilroy |first1=Joab |title=An Introduction to Auto Chess, Teamfight Tactics and Dota Underlords |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/07/04/a-guide-to-auto-chess-tft-league-of-legends-teamfight-tactics-dota-underlords |website=IGN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704045655/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/07/04/a-guide-to-auto-chess-tft-league-of-legends-teamfight-tactics-dota-underlords |archive-date=July 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A match features up to eight players online who take turns playing against each other in a one-on-one format, with the winner being the final player standing after eliminating all of the opposing heroes.<ref name=\"EGrules\">{{cite web |last1=Makar |first1=Connor |title=Dota Underlords guide: Strategies for how to play Dota Underlords, from getting gold to when to buy XP and unit upgrades |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-07-08-dota-underlords-guide-how-to-play-strategies-6037 |website=Eurogamer |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709212250/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-07-08-dota-underlords-guide-how-to-play-strategies-6037 |archive-date=July 9, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to the online [[matchmaking]], single-player matches against [[Video game bot|bots]] is also featured, as well as a \"freestyle\" practice mode that puts no limits on hero combinations.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/><ref name=\"Duos\">{{cite web |last1=Tan Guan Hao |first1=Dexter |title=Dota Underlords gets 2 new game modes for The Big Update |url=https://dotesports.com/dota-2/news/dota-underlords-gets-two-new-game-modes-for-the-big-update |website=Dot Esports |accessdate=October 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022173448/https://dotesports.com/dota-2/news/dota-underlords-gets-two-new-game-modes-for-the-big-update |archive-date=October 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Over the course of a match, players earn gold and [[experience points]], which are used to upgrade heroes and other playable units to make them stronger.<ref name=\"EGrules\"/> Players also make use of [[Item (gaming)|items]], which give stat bonuses to units.<ref name=\"EGrules\"/> The game also features a \"duos\" mode, allowing two players on separate boards, but sharing health and levels, to perform as a team, with the winning duo having the best combined damage totals by the end.<ref name=\"Duos\"/>\n\n==Development and release==\n''Dota Underlords'' was developed and published by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[macOS]], [[Microsoft Windows]], and [[Linux]]. It is based on ''[[Dota Auto Chess]]'', a popular community created game mode within ''[[Dota 2]]'', a game they also developed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bolding |first1=Jonathan |title=A Dota 2 custom mode may be 2019's most popular new game |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/a-dota-2-custom-mode-may-be-2019s-most-popular-new-game/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190122195616/https://www.pcgamer.com/a-dota-2-custom-mode-may-be-2019s-most-popular-new-game/ |archive-date=January 22, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Warr |first1=Philippa |title=Dota Auto Chess: The joyful deck-based Dota 2 game that Artifact isn't |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-auto-chess-the-joyful-deck-based-dota-2-game-that-artifact-isnt/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=February 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190208131821/https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-auto-chess-the-joyful-deck-based-dota-2-game-that-artifact-isnt/ |archive-date=February 8, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Sullivan |first1=Lucas |title=The skyrocketing rise of Auto Chess, a Dota 2 custom map that became one of the year's biggest games |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/dota-auto-chess/ |website=GamesRadar+ |accessdate=April 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412164930/https://www.gamesradar.com/dota-auto-chess/ |archive-date=April 12, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Following ''Dota Auto Chess''{{'s}} release in January 2019, it quickly become a phenomenon, having over seven million players by April 2019, Valve had met with the mod's developers, the Chinese-based Drodo Studio, to discuss directly collaborating on a standalone version. However, the two companies were unable to come to an agreement, with them both stating that it was in their best interest to develop their own separate games, with ''Dota Underlords'' being Valve's project.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gilliam |first1=Ryan |title=Auto Chess creators bringing stand-alone game to PC later this year |url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/10/18660080/auto-chess-pc-epic-game-store-pc-gaming-show-e3-2019 |website=Polygon |accessdate=June 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611121202/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/10/18660080/auto-chess-pc-epic-game-store-pc-gaming-show-e3-2019 |archive-date=June 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The game was built using Valve's [[Source 2]] game engine, making it the first game using that engine to be released on mobile platforms.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bailey |first1=Dustin |title=The Dota Underlords open beta is now live |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/open-beta |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710192913/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/open-beta |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nValve announced ''Dota Underlords'' in May 2019, with it releasing in [[early access]] as a [[free-to-play]] game on June 20, 2019.<ref>{{cite web | last = Grayson | first = Nathan | title = Valve Is Making Its Own Version Of Dota Auto Chess | date = May 20, 2019 | url = https://kotaku.com/valve-is-making-its-own-version-of-dota-auto-chess-1834934135 | website = Kotaku | accessdate = May 21, 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190522173226/https://kotaku.com/valve-is-making-its-own-version-of-dota-auto-chess-1834934135 | archive-date = May 22, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Valve's Auto Chess competitor is Dota Underlords |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/13/18678182/dota-underlords-valve-auto-chess-open-beta-platforms |website=Polygon |accessdate=June 13, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190613222336/https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/13/18678182/dota-underlords-valve-auto-chess-open-beta-platforms |archive-date=June 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> where it saw over 1.5 million downloads and held a [[concurrent player count]] on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] of over 200,000 within a few days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Minotti |first1=Mike |title=Sensor Tower: Dota Underlords sees 1.5 million downloads in first week |url=https://venturebeat.com/2019/06/28/sensor-tower-dota-underlords-sees-1-5-million-downloads-in-first-week/ |website=VentureBeat |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630223055/https://venturebeat.com/2019/06/28/sensor-tower-dota-underlords-sees-1-5-million-downloads-in-first-week/ |archive-date=June 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Ali |title=Dota Underlords' player count tops 200,000 in its opening weekend |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/player-count-update |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710184350/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/player-count-update |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Features such as a replay system, ranked [[matchmaking]], daily challenges and rewards, and a [[battle pass]] were added over time during its early access phase before it officially released on February 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dota Underlords update: what features are coming to Underlords soon? |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/update |website=PCGamesN |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710184355/https://www.pcgamesn.com/dota-underlords/update |archive-date=July 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Connor |first1=Alice |title=Dota Underlords rises out of early access today |url=https://venturebeat.com/2020/02/25/dota-underlords-season-one-kicks-off-with-battle-pass-and-more/ |website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref> It features full [[cross-platform play]] between its PC and mobile versions, with players able to freely start games on one and finish it on another.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lawler |first1=Richard |title=Valve's 'Dota Underlords' open beta launches on Android, iOS and PC |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/20/dota-underlords-beta/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624140452/https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/20/dota-underlords-beta/ |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]'' called it a clone of ''Dota Auto Chess'', stating that while they thought ''Underlords'' was more appealing to new players, the many similarities to the original mod could make it hard for veterans of the genre to see a reason to play ''Underlords'' over it, adding that games need to be more \"unique in order to survive\" in a niche genre.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gillia |first1=Ryan |title=Dota Underlords feels like a clone of Auto Chess |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/21/18683816/dota-underlords-auto-chess-clone |website=Polygon |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630042648/https://www.polygon.com/2019/6/21/18683816/dota-underlords-auto-chess-clone |archive-date=June 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Critics also compared and contrasted it with ''[[Artifact (video game)|Artifact]]'', another Valve-developed ''Dota'' spinoff game released around the same time that was seen as unsuccessful,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Fraser |title=Dota Underlords has more than double Artifact's peak player count |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-underlords-has-more-than-double-artifacts-peak-player-count/ |website=PC Gamer |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623155728/https://www.pcgamer.com/dota-underlords-has-more-than-double-artifacts-peak-player-count/ |archive-date=June 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lawler |first1=Richard |title='Dota Underlords' has more people playing now than 'Artifact' ever did |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/21/dota-underlords/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624145532/http://www.engadget.com/2019/06/21/dota-underlords/ |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Grayson |first1=Nathan |title=Valve's New Auto Chess Game Is Already Way More Popular Than Artifact Ever Was |url=https://kotaku.com/valves-new-auto-chess-game-is-already-way-more-popular-1835739847 |website=Kotaku |accessdate=July 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624125634/https://kotaku.com/valves-new-auto-chess-game-is-already-way-more-popular-1835739847 |archive-date=June 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> as well as ''[[Teamfight Tactics]]'', the ''[[League of Legends]]'' take on the genre.<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ye |first1=Josh |title=Auto battlers started with Dota Auto Chess and now Valve and Riot Games are joining in |url=https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/auto-battlers-started-dota-auto-chess-and-now-valve-and-riot-games-are-joining/article/3017888 |website=Abacus |accessdate=July 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717000924/https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/auto-battlers-started-dota-auto-chess-and-now-valve-and-riot-games-are-joining/article/3017888 |archive-date=July 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[IGN]]'' considered ''Underlords'' to be the easiest auto battler to get into as a novice due in part to its [[user interface]].<ref name=\"AutobattlerIGN\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.underlords.com/}}\n\n{{Dota}}\n{{Valve}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games}}\n\n[[Category:2020 video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Auto battler video games]]\n[[Category:Dota]]\n[[Category:Esports games]]\n[[Category:Fantasy video games]]\n[[Category:Free online games]]\n[[Category:Free-to-play video games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Linux games]]\n[[Category:Lua-scripted video games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Strategy video games]]\n[[Category:Source 2 games]]\n[[Category:Valve Corporation games]]\n[[Category:Video games containing battle passes]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games with cross-platform play]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Video games that support Vulkan]]\n", "name_user": "Dissident93", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGameplay", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dota_Underlords"}
